#create own color schemes
col1     <- colorRampPalette(c("blue", "lightblue","yellow", "red", "red4")) 
col2     <- colorRampPalette(c("darkblue", "blue", "lightblue","yellow", "red", "red4")) 

#continents and oceans polygons
pols1 <- list("sp.polygons", as(oceans, 'SpatialPolygons'), fill = gray(0.99), lwd = 0.1)
pols2 <- list("sp.polygons", as(land,   'SpatialPolygons'), fill = gray(0.8), lwd = 0.1)


Figures 3, 4, S8 (leaf freezing resistance and leaf-out)

#########################
#leaf freezing resistance
#########################

frost <- model.layers.stack[[3]]
brks1 <- seq(0,1,0.01) 
frost <- disaggregate(frost, fact=2, method="bilinear")


#############################
#leaf-out date biomes 4 and 8
#############################

leafout <- model.layers.stack[[8]]
leafout[leafout>116] = 116
leafout[leafout<98] = 98
brks2 <- seq(98,116,0.1) 
leafout <- disaggregate(leafout, fact=2, method="bilinear")


#############################
#leaf-out date biomes 5 and 6
#############################

leafout56 <- model.layers.stack[[9]]
leafout56[leafout56>140] = 140
leafout56[leafout56<115] = 116
brks4 <- seq(115,140,0.1) 
leafout56 <- disaggregate(leafout56, fact=2, method="bilinear")


###################
#leaf-out variation
###################

leafoutSD <- model.layers.stack[[15]]
leafoutSD[leafoutSD>11] = 11
leafoutSD[leafoutSD<7] = 7
brks3 <- seq(7,11,0.01) 
leafoutSD <- disaggregate(leafoutSD, fact=2, method="bilinear")


#######
# Plots
#######

frost = spplot(frost, 
       at = round(brks1, digits=2), 
       maxpixels=2*ncell(frost),
       col.regions = (col1(length(brks1))),
       sp.layout=list(pols1, pols2),
       main = list(label='Figure 3 (leaf freezing resistance)',cex=0.7),
       colorkey = list(space = "right"))
leafout = spplot(leafout, 
       at = round(brks2, digits=2), 
       maxpixels=2*ncell(leafout),
       col.regions = (col2(length(brks2))),
       sp.layout=list(pols1, pols2),
       main = list(label='Figure 4a (leaf-out date)',cex=0.7),
       colorkey = list(space = "right"))
leafoutSD = spplot(leafoutSD, 
       at = round(brks3, digits=2), 
       maxpixels=2*ncell(leafoutSD),
       col.regions = rev(col1(length(brks3))),
       sp.layout=list(pols1, pols2),
       main = list(label='Figure 4b (leaf-out variation)',cex=0.7),
       colorkey = list(space = "right"))
leafout56 = spplot(leafout56, 
         at = round(brks4, digits=2), 
         maxpixels=2*ncell(leafout56),
         col.regions = (col2(length(brks4))),
         sp.layout=list(pols1, pols2),
         main = list(label='Figure S8 (leaf-out date coniferous forests)',cex=0.7),
         colorkey = list(space = "right"))

pdf(paste(output.dir,"Figure3,4,S8.pdf",sep="/"), width=8, height=16)

dev.off()

Figures 5 and S7 (frost damage risk)

map       <- model.layers.stack[[3]]
map2      <- model.layers.stack[[3]]
frost     <- model.layers.stack[[3]]
leafout   <- model.layers.stack[[10]]
leafoutSD <- model.layers.stack[[15]]


######################
#Freezing threshold 0C
######################

# Significant decrease in LSF
map[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 2

# No change in LSF
map[complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>=0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 3

# Significant increase in LSF
map[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 4

# Significant increase in LSF and low leaf freezing resistance
map[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.25] = 5

# Significant increase in LSF, low leaf freezing resistance, early leaf-out, and high leaf-out variation
map[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.25 
    & leafout < 108 
    & leafoutSD > 8.5] = 6

# Strong increase in LSF, low leaf freezing resistance, early leaf-out, and high leaf-out variation
map[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.45 
    & leafout < 108
    & leafoutSD > 8.5 
    & complete.layers[["Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>3] = 7

map[map<2] = 2


#######################
#Freezing threshold -4C
#######################

# Significant decrease in LSF
map2[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 2

# No change in LSF
map2[complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster"]]>=0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 3

# Significant increase in LSF
map2[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > -1] = 4

# Significant increase in LSF and low leaf freezing resistance
map2[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.25] = 5

# Significant increase in LSF, low leaf freezing resistance, early leaf-out, and high leaf-out variation
map2[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.25 
    & leafout < 108 
    & leafoutSD > 8.5] = 6

# Strong increase in LSF, low leaf freezing resistance, early leaf-out, and high leaf-out variation
map2[complete.layers[["Tau_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]>0 
    & complete.layers[["Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster"]]<0.1 
    & frost > 0.45 
    & leafout < 108
    & leafoutSD > 8.5

brks5 <- seq(2,7,0.01) 
map3 = map
map4 = map2
map  = disaggregate(map, fact=2, method="bilinear")
map2 = disaggregate(map2, fact=2, method="bilinear")

frostRisk = spplot(map, 
       at          = round(brks5, digits=2),

extremeFrostRisk = spplot(map2, 
         at          = round(brks5, digits=2), 
         maxpixels   = 2*ncell(map),
         col.regions = (col2(length(brks5))),
         sp.layout   = list(pols1, pols2),

##############
# Create table
##############


all.layers = stack(map3, map4, complete.layers[["WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree"]])
datat      = as.data.frame(all.layers, xy=T)
datat      = na.omit(datat)


# Continent intersection
########################

coordinates(datat)  = c("x", "y") # coordinates to intersect
datat$continent     = over(x=datat, y=continents) # intersection
datat               = as.data.frame(datat) # converts the data to dataframe again
datat               = na.omit(datat)


# Delete continents and create new continent column
###################################################

datat               <- datat[complete.cases(datat$CONTINENT) & 
                               datat$CONTINENT!="Africa" & 
                               datat$CONTINENT!="Antarctica" & 
                               datat$CONTINENT!="Australia",]

datat$continent_sub <- ifelse(datat$CONTINENT=="North America", "North America", 
                             ifelse(datat$CONTINENT=="Europe", "Europe", 
                                   ifelse(datat$CONTINENT=="South America", "South America",
                                         ifelse(datat$x<80, "West Asia", "East Asia"))))


# Get pixel area
################

area_map  = raster::area(map) #create area map
datat     = data.frame(datat, #extract area information
                       pixelArea = raster::extract(area_map, datat[, c("x", "y")])) 


# Merge continent and biome identifier
######################################

datat$mix <- paste(datat$continent_sub, datat$WWF_Biomes_HalfDegree, sep="_")


#####################################################
# Relative area (%) in which frost risk is increasing
#####################################################

total_area   = aggregate(datat$pixelArea, 
                         by=list(Category=datat$mix), 
                         FUN=sum)

############
# Frost risk
############

Increase     = 1-(aggregate(datat[datat$MeanFrost_ML_Predicted_Raster_for_all_biome_merged.1 < 6, ]
                         $pixelArea, 
                         by=list(Category=datat[datat$MeanFrost_ML_Predicted_Raster_for_all_biome_merged.1 < 6, ]
                                 $mix), 
                         FUN=sum)[2] / total_area[2])

#create table
tab           = cbind(total_area[1], Increase)
names(tab)    = c("Mix", "Increase")
tab           = separate(tab, col = "Mix", into = c("continent", "biome"), sep = "_")
tab$continent = factor(tab$continent, 
                       levels=c("North America", "South America", "Europe", "West Asia", "East Asia"), 
                       ordered=T)
tab$biome     = factor(tab$biome, 
                       levels=c(8,4,5,6), 
                       ordered=T)

#write table
write.table(tab, file=paste(output.dir, "frost_risk_change.csv", sep="/"), 
            col.names=TRUE, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, sep=",")

frostRisk = ggplot(tab, aes(x=continent, y=Increase*100, fill=biome)) +
  geom_bar(colour="black", stat="identity", position=position_dodge()) +
  annotate("rect", xmin=-Inf, xmax=1.5, ymin=-Inf, ymax=Inf, fill="grey80", alpha=0.1) +
  annotate("rect", xmin=1.5, xmax=2.5, ymin=-Inf, ymax=Inf, fill="grey30", alpha=0.1) +
  annotate("rect", xmin=2.5, xmax=3.5, ymin=-Inf, ymax=Inf, fill="grey80", alpha=0.1) +
  annotate("rect", xmin=3.5, xmax=4.5, ymin=-Inf, ymax=Inf, fill="grey30", alpha=0.1) +
  annotate("rect", xmin=4.5, xmax=Inf, ymin=-Inf, ymax=Inf, fill="grey80", alpha=0.1) +
  geom_bar(colour="black", stat="identity", position=position_dodge()) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(5,55))+
  labs(x = "Continent", y = "Threatened area (%)") +
  ggtitle("Inset Fig. 5: Frost risk") +
  theme(#legend.position= "NA",
        legend.background = element_rect(fill=NA, 
                                         size=0.5, linetype="solid"),
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = 'white', colour = 'black'))
